      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i need some help writing an email. we had a candidate for a senior dev role reach the final round but we decided to go with someone else. they were actually really good and had great technical skills, so i dont want to burn the bridge, but it needs to be professional and firm. can u help me draft a rejection email?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Hey there! I'd be happy to help you draft that email. Since this is a sensitive situation involving a talented candidate, it's great that you want to maintain a professional relationship.\n\nHere is a draft you can use, keeping it firm yet respectful:\n\n**Subject:** Update Regarding Your Application for Senior Developer Role\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you for taking the time to interview with us and for the insightful discussion regarding the Senior Developer position. We truly appreciated your technical expertise and the quality of your contributions during the final round.\n\nAfter careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose experience aligns slightly more closely with our immediate project needs. We were impressed by your skills and would love to keep you in mind for future opportunities that match your profile.\n\nWe hope you understand our decision and wish you the best in your job search. Please feel free to reach out if you have any questions.\n\nBest regards,\n\n[Your Name]\n[Your Title]\n\n***\n\n**A quick note on the tone:** This draft strikes a balance between gratitude and clarity. It acknowledges their strength (which is crucial for not burning the bridge) while firmly stating the decision was made.\n\n**One final thought:**",
