      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks that works. but i think a bit more warmth would be good. like, maybe mention that the competition was really intense this time around and it was a tough call for the team. can you add a sentence or two about how impressed the whole panel was with them specifically? just makes it feel less like a template.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That is a fantastic idea, and adding that layer of warmth will definitely make the email feel much more human and less like a cold corporate template. It's a great way to show that the decision wasn't made lightly, even though the candidate was excellent.\n\nHere is the revised draft with those specific additions, keeping the tone warm but professional:\n\n**Subject:** Update Regarding Your Application for Senior Developer Role\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you for taking the time to interview with us and for the insightful discussion regarding the Senior Developer position. We truly appreciated your technical expertise and the quality of your contributions during the final round.\n\nWe want to be completely transparent: the competition for this role was incredibly intense, and it was a genuinely tough call for the entire panel. We were absolutely blown away by your performance; in fact, every member of the hiring committee expressed how impressed they were with your specific skills and problem-solving approach. It was a close race, but we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose experience aligns slightly more closely with our immediate project needs.\n\nWe were so impressed by you that we would love to keep you in mind for future opportunities that match your profile. We hope you understand our decision and wish you the",
